metadata.title: Beechcraft Super King Air
aws::graph::propositions: Beechcraft Super King Air Models and Variants
Later models of Beechcraft Super King Air were fitted with Pro Line 21 avionics.
A total of 65 aircraft similar in specification to the B200C were built for the U.S. military.
Model B200T is a version of B200 similar to Model 200T.
Model B200T aircraft were converted from Model B200s.
Model B200T aircraft were re-serialled.
23 Model B200T aircraft were delivered.
Model B200CT is a version of B200C with wingtip fuel tanks.
All Model B200CT aircraft were converted from B200Cs.
All Model B200CT aircraft were re-serialled.
Eight Model B200CT aircraft were delivered.
Model B200CT aircraft were delivered to the Marina de Guerra del Perú.
Model B200CT aircraft were delivered to the Israeli Air Force.
Another two aircraft similar to Model B200CT were built for the Israeli Air Force.
The two similar aircraft built for the Israeli Air Force are without an official designation.
Model B200 is marketed as King Air 250.
Model B200 includes new Hartzell composite scimitar propellers.
Model B200 includes third-party winglets.
Model B200 includes Ram Air Recovery System.
Model B200 can operate from shorter runways than the B200GT.
Model B200GT is an updated version of B200.
Model B200GT is the current civil production model.

text:
Later models fitted with Pro Line 21 avionics. A total of 65 other aircraft, similar in specification to the B200C, were built for the U.S. military.
Model B200T
Version of B200 similar to Model 200T; aircraft converted from Model B200s and re-serialled. 23 delivered.
Model B200CT
Version of B200C with wingtip fuel tanks; all aircraft converted from B200Cs and re-serialled. Eight delivered, to the Marina de Guerra del Perú and Israeli Air Force. Another two similar aircraft built for the Israeli Air Force are without an official designation.
Model B200 (marketed as King Air 250)
Includes new Hartzell composite scimitar propellers and third-party winglets and Ram Air Recovery System; can operate from shorter runways than the B200GT.
Model B200GT
Updated version of B200; current civil production model.
